videos.title: Learn Debounce And Throttle
videos.description: Debounce and throttle are two easy techniques to implement that will drastically increase the performance of any site that has heavy API usage. In this video I show you how to implement both techniques, compare the pros/cons of each, and give real world examples of when to use each technique.

videos.title: Null and Undefined Difference
videos.description: Learn about the difference between null and undefined in JavaScript.

videos.title: JavaScript Event Loop: How it Works
videos.description: One of the most important concepts to learn in JavaScript! The Event Loop is core to how JavaScript handles asynchronous code. In this video, we'll break down the call stack, event loop, and event queue to show you how JavaScript works under the hood.

options.option: A search bar where the results are displayed as you type.

quizzes.question: What is the difference between null and undefined in JavaScript?
quizzes.video_title: #2 JavaScript Tips and Tricks - JavaScript Job Interview Questions

options.option: null represents the intentional absence of any object value.
undefined represents the uninitialized value of a variable or property.
